			<div class="content" id="post-content-4859930">
									

<p>Something or someone is censoring information on foundation database and it is spreading to all known copies including pyhsical ones.</p>
<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights</strong>: Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout:</strong> Classic article</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> Idea is that something is &quot;corrupting&quot; Foundation database with random censors like ████ or [DATA REDACTED] while the censored information was known before and cant be find anywhere including any physical copies of it. This phenomenon is somehow spreading to other articles.</p>
<p>At first look it may look like a error or maybe GoI spies, but with some logical explanations and different theories threat is something different.</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative</strong>: It gives several theories and hypothesis about whats the reason or whats the behind it after the discovery. Discovery of it starts by junior researcher that leads to researcher collague to the site director after they agree its not a simple error and at the final to the one of the O5's. With that investigations start with help of web crawlers.</p>
<p>In short central narrative will be about its discovery and leads to its current state (with some dialogues), while foundation giving several theories about what or how this is happening and why.(With table wizard)</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
