<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> So we know that somehow SCP-XXXX corrupts database but how we can be sure that it didnt corrupt this article. (Lets call it Article A) Answer is simple but effective. If there is any censor in article there must be a explanation for it to know that file is corrupted or not.</p>
<p>example: Solution is [DATA REDACTED] (It has been censored due to being possible cognitohazard.)</p>
<p>In article it says this censor effects everyone except Ethics Comittee. (Including O-5's) There are 2 different reasons for it. 1st one is; we know that ethics comittee can read all type of censor hence it doesnt affect them somehow.</p>
<p>2nd reason is much more radical, and this scp is nothing but Ethics Comittee doing. Why would they do that you may think? Reason is they want to gain upper-hand againsts O-5's on power shift between them. They know that they are on constant power war. They know that they can censor everything they want and no one would question them.</p>
</div>
