<p>The elevator pitch is a bit long, and as a reader, it’s a giant block of text that I don’t want to engage with. The elevator pitch, in general, is a sales pitch. You; as a writer, are selling us; the readers, on reading the piece- and to engage with the post. Sell us; the readers, on the article. Show us why we should take the time to read it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I like the hook and concept, but other than that this is lacking too much narrative for me to care as a reader to read the article if it were on the mainlist.</p>

