<p>I made the central narrative about the discovery of said SCP, how it was discovered by an accident with some junior researcher the dialogue between the researches and how it did happen or why it is happening. Then it goes to senior researcher from there to a site manager and when site manager realizes this is not a simple error in a database but something is happening on the whole database it goes to foundation web crawlers and announcing it scp at last.</p>
<p>GoI agents and others are few theories that made by foundation web crawlers at first to understand whats going on with this. Naturally they think it can be enemy spies or some kind of major error instead of anomaly but with some logical error that i stated above it doesnt make that much of a sense for them.</p>
<p>At the start and overall in the whole paragraph there are some few clues about this is all Ethics Comittee doing. These are some minor things like why this &quot;thing&quot; doesnt effect them or why one of the solutions/theories about the said scp is removed by Ethics Comittee.</p>
<p>So instead of giving a direct proposal about Ethics Commitee is going blackmail/overthrow O5-Council i thought that adding a little mystery and clues to reader something fishy is going on the article with Ethics Comittee.</p>
<p>At the end of a paragraph our reader (you) is getting a message after finishing the file, and it says that while showing examples from the read paragraph if you didnt notice something fishy is going on and claims something much much bigger than you is happening on the foundations top levels. I am skeptical around this because this has to be the major turn on the whole article so i may deliver it in another way or change the said message a bit different, like how did this guy reach you?</p>
<p>About the narrative lacking, i though it shouldnt be explained that much except its being something anomolous with censoring on foundation database, instead of that i wanted to give how it was discovered and realized to its current state and some theories of what might be or not be with their explanations to them.</p>

