<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>On a side note to be more specific about theories goes like this: After the initial discovery by junior researcher it goes to collague and his mentor researcher from there they realize something weird or even anomolous goes on. After deciding this researcher goes to site manager and when site manager realizes there is indeed a problem and this effects whole database he/she contacs with one of the O5's to work up with foundation web crawlers.</p>
<p>This all discovery part is created by dialogues between them with some normal kind of explaning.</p>
<p>After the discovery phase, research led by one of the O5's with foundation web crawlers they lay out some theories and any reasons if it can be possible or not like GoI spies. I thought writing them in box style like in SCP-5000 and to the next box reasons of them.</p>
<p>As i mentioned above the last box thingy (dont remember the exact name of it, bracklets?) of theory gets removed by comittee for so called &quot;cognitohazard&quot;</p>
<p>After all these discovery, dialogues between foundation personal and the final conclusion about this being an scp as a result of web crawlers research all these different theories laid on box style.</p>
<hr /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Also at the end of it with all these minor clues i thought about some part like: You have 1 new message! With collapsibles or something similar with that.</p>
<p>You can like click on the message and someone tells you while showing all the clues in the text if you missed or didnt understand them with the reasonings. He/She tells you that infact this isnt a scp but a committes doing from the start, and gives you explaning why would committee do that.</p>
<p>This mysterious person obviously knows that you are not gonna believe him/her straightforward but gives you more of a &quot;guidance&quot;<br />
to seek truths about all this. He does know that you are currently working for several weeks now on the reason and spread of the said scp and hence knows you dont need to take amnestics, for now.</p>
<p>Maybe this mysterious person is one of the web crawlers? Maybe junior researcher that found it and forced to blackmail by Committee that seeks revenge? Maybe the O5 that started investigations with web crawlers and tries to stay low profile?</p>
<p>But you dont get any more answers, person that wrote you the message wishes you best of luck and finishes his message.</p>
<p>So at the conclusion, reader may find some clues about the Comittee in the file and raise some questions about them but they can also miss or catch all of them too. It depends on viewer perspective at this point i guess. So i tried to make some of them quite obvious while making other ones more secretive in a sense.</p>
<p>And at the end doesnt mattering the result of that if reader catch any clues or not, the twist and story about Committee trying to blackmail/gain upper hand against O5's will be laid out and none of the users will miss it if they press you have 1 message! thing or something similar to that.</p>
<p>-So if user got all clues great for them! They can get satisfacted by the end results</p>
<p>-Lets say user user got some of them and missed the rest, by this the user can go back to reading to check about the other clues in the article about what they missed if they are curious to explore more.</p>
<p>-Or the third option is that, our user missed all of the clues or didnt have any idea about something fishy is going on article. (I really plan to make one of the hints easily understandable just because of this reason) Well maybe they can re-read it from start or read it more carefully because i really think that, it <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">can be</span> should be visible to be understand something weird is going on with this article if read carefully while raising some questions to theories, discovery, amnestics requirement, update by comittee etc.</p>
<p>In option 1 and 2 it can easily lead something is going on but cant tell what it is exactly.<br />
I really hope that this final message sent by mysterious person will be the final delivery and satistaction on theme.<br />
And about option 3 i really think this is unlikely, unless the person didnt read the all story carefully.</p>
<p>On a final sidenote about clues, i am thinking about something like before starting the file; WARNING! BEFORE READING CURRENT FILE UNLESS YOU ARE AN ON-GOING WORK PERSONAL ABOUT SAID SCP, YOU MUST TAKE CLASS-A AMNESTICS AFTER READING.</p>
<p>collapsible YOU MAY ADVANCE</p>
<p>So from the start, even before reading the file they <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">will</span> must know something weird is going on with this SCP</p>
