			<div class="content" id="post-content-4862749">
									

<p>About question 1;</p>
<p>EC wants to take over Council because they think that they are not following their own principles such as &quot;Foundation is not cruel but cold&quot;. They are always standing a ground against every single unnecessary cruel decision they take to keep them in balance.</p>
<p>Its also known that from multiple SCP Articles they are fighting for a power between them and finding a clever solution to that behind their back with some made-up SCP is perfect opportunity for them to get ahead of them.</p>
<p>About question 2 and 3;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I thought about putting these possibilities at first glance however; Adding all these possibilities/ways is a bit overwhelming for a SCP but might be better fit for a tale.</p>
<p>This SCP is about a made-up censor SCP ,while putting clues for reader to think/suspect about something, by E.C to gain critical information about Council to takeover/blackmail them while they dont even realize whats going on.</p>
<p>Adding about how E.C will takeover Council, if they are going to be succesful or not, what will happen if they can/cant is a bit much about this article and will change everything from the start.</p>
<p>Instead of this adding a interactive tale (like there are given options to reader what to do and these options are going to change ending result) while slowly showing the &quot;genius plan&quot; of E.C how they will take over, if our reader going to side with E.C or Council, what will happen at the end if they will be succesfull or not is a better option instead of adding all this to 1 single SCP.</p>
<p>But of course thats my opinion afterall and that was the reason why i didnt include anything about 2nd or 3th question.</p>
<p>Even if we share different options on this, i value your critism very much and thank you for giving a read about all his.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

